PN,35904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1782564485
OL,3,CNearly three years in prison for carer
OL,4,Cwho stole pensioner's life savings
OL,6,FDe Sousa was in a managerial position
OL,7,Ffor Aurum Home Care where she was also
OL,8,Fthe victim's home carer.
OL,10,FThe pensioner gave De Sousa her debit
OL,11,Fcard to buy household items. Instead,
OL,12,Fshe used it to purchase luxury
OL,13,Fproducts such as an Apple Watch, a
OL,14,Fjuicer, and various cosmetics.
OL,16,FDe Sousa also bought #149 of food from
OL,17,FIceland, including dog food.
OL,19,FHer crimes were first detected after
OL,20,Fthe victim's bank alerted her to
OL,21,Fsuspicious activity.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/8
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,360,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1782564485
OL,3,CNearly three years in prison for carer
OL,4,Cwho stole pensioner's life savings
OL,6,FAfter questioning De Sousa, some of
OL,7,Fthe items that appeared on the
OL,8,Fvictim's bank transactions were seen
OL,9,Fin her house.
OL,11,FDe Sousa's defence lawyer told the
OL,12,Fcourt before sentencing that she now
OL,13,Faccepts her wrongdoing and that, at
OL,14,Fthe time of her offending, her mental
OL,15,Fhealth was at rock bottom.
OL,17,FThe court also heard how she was under
OL,18,Fsignificant financial pressure in
OL,19,Fcaring for her three children, and
OL,20,Flived with rental debts of around
OL,21,F#17,000.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/8
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,360,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1782564485
OL,3,CNearly three years in prison for carer
OL,4,Cwho stole pensioner's life savings
OL,6,FIn his sentencing remarks, Judge Mark
OL,7,FTemple KC described De Sousa's crimes
OL,8,Fas a "profound breach of trust".
OL,10,FThe judge added, "You stole almost all
OL,11,Fof her money, and those who care for
OL,12,Fthe elderly need to understand if they
OL,13,Fbetray them, they will receive a
OL,14,Fcustodial sentence."
OL,16,FFollowing the sentencing, PC Jessica
OL,17,FBrown from the States of Jersey Police
OL,18,Fissued a statement commending the
OL,19,Fsentencing and the bravery of the
OL,20,Fvictim.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/8
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,360,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1782564485
OL,3,CNearly three years in prison for carer
OL,4,Cwho stole pensioner's life savings
OL,6,F"Fraud can have a significant impact
OL,7,Fon victims, causing financial loss as
OL,8,Fwell as considerable stress and
OL,9,Fanxiety," PC Brown states.
OL,11,F"This sentence reflects the
OL,12,Fseriousness of the offence and
OL,13,Fdemonstrates that those who commit
OL,14,Ffraud will be held accountable for
OL,15,Ftheir actions.
OL,17,F"The court heard that the offender
OL,18,Fabused the trust of being a carer and
OL,19,Fpreyed on the victim's trustworthy
OL,20,Fnature.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/8
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,360,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1782564485
OL,3,CNearly three years in prison for carer
OL,4,Cwho stole pensioner's life savings
OL,6,F"The court also heard the impact that
OL,7,Fthis case has had on the victim, to
OL,8,Fwhich I would like to thank the victim
OL,9,Ffor her trust and bravery to come
OL,10,Fforward and courage to give evidence
OL,11,Fin court."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/8
